The paper discusses the security issues related to the ADS-B protocol, which is a communication protocol used in air transportation systems. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses theoretical and practical efforts to address these security issues, which could fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
